valueMarkdown.value: Note that the terminologies included in this implementation guide will need to be updated, because the ideal mechanism for distribution (as an expression) is not currently supported by the content logical definition constructs available in the FHIR ValueSet resource and all known implementations of it. Before use in a production environment, ensure you have the latest value sets based on the definitions for each value set (as defined in the inclusion/exclusion criteria for each one).

title.value: Snomed and ICD10 Malignant or Pacreatic Cancers or Hepatic Failure

publisher.value: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)

description.value: ValueSet containing conditions that generally are thought to have terminal prognosis.

display.value: Clinical Focus

text.value: Conditions that generally are thought to have terminal prognosis.

display.value: United States of America

purpose.value: Used to determine if patient is diagnosed with a terminal condition as part of the patient's end of life assessment workflow in all recommendations.

valueString.value: set delimiter = " "; FROM [^SNOMED CT US Edition^] with (CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF_PLUS "Secondary malignant neoplastic disease (disorder)" OR CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF_PLUS "Malignant tumor of pancreas (disorder)" OR CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF_PLUS "Hepatic failure (disorder)") EXPORT Concept_Name,^Code in Source[SNOMED CT US Edition]^,^Parent^; set delimiter = " "; FROM [^ICD-10-CM^] with (CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF "[C25] Malignant neoplasm of pancreas[ICD-10-CM]" OR CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF "[C76-C80] Malignant neoplasms of ill-defined, other secondary and unspecified sites (C76-C80)[ICD-10-CM]" OR CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF "[K72] Hepatic failure, not elsewhere classified[ICD-10-CM]" OR CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF "[K70.4] Alcoholic hepatic failure[ICD-10-CM]") EXPORT ^Name^,^Code^;
